//
// test/Driver/diag-format-json-smoke.test — `--diagnostic-format=json`
// smoke test (US3 / Phase 5 / T066).
//
// Per /speckit-clarify Q2 (M1 ships smoke-only NDJSON; full schema
// lock + per-kind round-trip + LSP consumer all defer to T3),
// this fixture asserts ONLY the NDJSON shape: one valid JSON object
// per line with the five mandatory fields per
// `contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md` research §9.
// **No content equality** beyond the shape.

// RUN: printf '"unterminated\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc --diagnostic-format=json -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// One NDJSON line with the five mandatory fields. The path/line/col
// values can vary; we just assert the shape.
// CHECK: {"path":"{{.*}}","line":{{[0-9]+}},"col":{{[0-9]+}},"severity":"error","message":"unterminated string literal"}
